  "prompt": "What is the best web prototyping/mockup tool?",
  "response": "Choosing the best web prototyping/mockup tool can be subjective and depends largely on the specific needs and preferences of the user or team. However, some of the most popular and highly regarded tools in 2023 include:\n\n1. **Figma**: Known for its collaborative features, Figma allows multiple users to work on the same project simultaneously. It\u2019s highly favored for its ease of use, robust design tools, and cloud-based access.\n\n2. **Adobe XD**: A versatile tool that integrates well with other Adobe products. Adobe XD offers vector-based design and wireframing features and is great for creating high-fidelity prototypes.\n\n3. **Sketch**: Exclusively for macOS, Sketch is popular for its simplicity and efficiency in creating UI/UX designs. It has a large community and extensive plugin support.\n\n4. **InVision**: Renowned for its prototyping capabilities, InVision allows designers to create interactive mockups and collaborate with team members easily. It integrates seamlessly with other design tools.\n\n5. **Axure RP**: Known for its advanced prototyping features, Axure RP is ideal for detailed and functional mockups, including interactive and complex animations.\n\n6. **Marvel**: Another tool focused on simplicity and collaboration, Marvel is great for quick mockups and user testing. It\u2019s user-friendly and integrates well with other design tools.\n\nUltimately, the best tool will depend on your specific requirements like collaborative features, integration capabilities, ease of use, supported platforms, and the level of fidelity needed in your prototypes. Trying out a few of these tools can help determine which one aligns best with your project needs and workflow.",
